4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                               # Target

set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)      # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                             # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                            # Test Dataset

5.

Caution! Package "caret" Logistic Regression Target 2 , . , Factor (Level) . , a b 2 Target Factor a b, a, b .

fitControl <- trainControl(method = "cv", number = 5,  # 5-Fold Cross Validation (5-Fold CV)
                           allowParallel = TRUE)       #  

set.seed(100)                                          # For CV
logis.fit <- train(Personal.Loan ~ ., data = UB.trd, 
                   trControl = fitControl,
                   method = "glm",
                   family = "binomial",                # For Logit Transformation
                   preProc = c("center", "scale"))     # Standardization for

pp  <- as.numeric(test.logis.prob)                        #

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

logis.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")         # roc( class,  )
auc        <- round(auc(logis.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(logis.roc,   
         col="gray",                                      # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                                # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                           # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                              # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                            # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                         # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                              #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                      #    

#  ggroc() 
ggroc(logis.roc) +
annotate(geom = "text", x = 0.9, y = 1.0,
label = paste("AUC = ", auc),
size = 5,
color="red") +
theme_bw()

2) Package Epi

pacman::p_load("Epi")       
# install_version("etm", version = "1.1", repos = "http://cran.us.r-project.org")

ROC(pp, ac, plot = "ROC")                                  # ROC( ,  class)

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

logis.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                          # prediction( ,  class)    

logis.perf <- performance(logis.pred, "tpr", "fpr")       # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(logis.perf, col = "gray")                            # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(logis.pred, "auc")              # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values 
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
